06:30.820 --> 06:38.180
This is Daryl Lane. And Bill Vernon. The Pell Bar Cycle, a series of
interconnected novels written by Paul O. Williams, describes the beginnings of

06:38.180 --> 06:45.240
the rebuilding of civilization in Midwestern America a thousand years after a
nuclear holocaust. In The Breaking of North Wall, the first novel of the series,

06:45.480 --> 06:53.020
we learn that the inhabitable parts of America are people by various tribes
whose cultures are still quite primitive. The Pell Bar Tribe, for instance, is

06:53.020 --> 07:03.440
the most advanced. It is a matriarchal society which lives in the city of Pell
Barigan. Here Williams details the tribe's origin. I envision the Pell Bar, the

07:03.440 --> 07:17.080
Pell Bar, as a group that had been started by a woman named Amanda Pell, who had
been a, she's sort of a feminist. And she is a metallurgist, or was, for

07:17.080 --> 07:28.520
Caterpillar Tractor up in Peoria. But she survived the holocaust by the fact
that she was spelunking down in the Ozarks. And it would be quite natural for

07:28.520 --> 07:45.840
her to set up a feminist society. And I really, I sort of tried to create the
Pell Bar as a settled society with what you might call a nesting instinct. And a

07:45.840 --> 08:00.720
natural combination of self-protectiveness and non-aggressiveness, although
they're certainly capable of great destructiveness. But potentially, a settled

08:00.720 --> 08:10.860
place like that becomes a kind of mother of civilization. So that was what was
in my mind there. The more primitive tribes, such as the Shumai and the Sentani,

08:10.980 --> 08:25.520
are wandering tribes. I created the Shumai and Sentani out of my memories of,
well, in part, out of my memories of the conflict of Caesar and the Celts in

08:25.520 --> 08:41.200
Britain, the Shumai are very Celtic in their behavior because they're
enthusiastic, artistic, kind of reckless and unorganized, whereas the Sentani

08:41.200 --> 08:58.500
are much more Roman. They organize into their star band and do everything in a
pattern-organized way. And I invented some backgrounds for these groups. The

08:58.500 --> 09:16.580
Shumai, as offspring of the children of one farmer in southwestern Minnesota
named Aaron Schumacher, and the Sentani, the explorer scout troop led by Antonio

09:16.580 --> 09:28.440
Sentani, who was a watchmaker in Memphis who happened to have a love of Roman
history. And they were on a field trip to a coal mine in Tennessee and so

09:28.440 --> 09:38.140
escaped the Holocaust there and created their society along quite different
lines. Williams used historical precedents when he came up with the various

09:38.140 --> 09:52.680
weapons the tribes use. The weapons in the breaking of North Wall really come
out of local archaeology because during most of post-glacial Indian history in

09:52.680 --> 10:09.680
this area, the Indians were users of spears only fairly recently did they, well,
2,000 years ago, did they begin to develop bows and arrows. And that coincides

10:09.680 --> 10:20.000
with their becoming a more settled culture, adapting to agriculture and that
kind of thing. We asked Williams at what point he generated the origins of the

10:20.000 --> 10:30.980
tribes. The strange thing about it was I figured all of this stuff out after I
wrote the book, you know, said, aha, that's where it must have come from, rather

10:30.980 --> 10:43.480
than consciously adopting these things for the book. It might sound strange, but
anyway, that's how it happened. More about Paulo Williams on our next show.

10:44.580 --> 10:45.280
Thank you.

